<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-median-grouped" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Median (Grouped)</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_vkzapbqt">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_8wsm66bi">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_sawx5np3">
                        3.0 Statistics and Probability
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_phc5dabx">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_b8vvop9k">
                        3.1 Statistics 1
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_y855p9lc">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_gvum18ze">
                        Determine mean, mode and median of grouped and ungrouped data
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_dzkim5y5" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_tihg2yx3">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_pzlgq1b9" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_852vvdfc">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p xml:id="auto_bg4g4s3s" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_rn3uzv4w"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_t2wzbh40">
                        <p xml:id="auto_3jeyjnum">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand that the median of grouped data is estimated using cumulative frequency and interpolation.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_atj1st3q">
                        <p xml:id="auto_zqmqsmuj">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Calculate the median of grouped data using the formula Median = L + ((n/2 − CF) / F) × C.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_y2ljxhbd">
                        <p xml:id="auto_xaxw819s">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Apply the grouped median formula to real-world datasets and interpret the result.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_ptfv7h8a">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/median-grouped.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_xmbfprvq">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/step-by-step-guide_median-grouped.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />


    <introduction xml:id="auto_vqre33lp">
        <p xml:id="auto_qbxe5cst">
            When data is grouped, we cannot determine the exact middle value by simply counting. Instead, we use cumulative frequencies to locate the median class and then use interpolation to estimate the median value.
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Problem-Solving and Discovery</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_bndoqikf">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_r3t6s90j">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_lbl20r7u">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_pwied1rb">Students work in groups to discover cumulative frequency and identify the median class for grouped data.</p>
            </li>
        </dl>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Discussion Prompts</title>
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_58e20a4q"><p xml:id="auto_lmcy4cpk">How many students are there in total?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_osrmsy9d"><p xml:id="auto_obaplvxt">Which student is in the middle position? (Hint: Total ÷ 2)</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_1f4nhvxd"><p xml:id="auto_cjy4trug">How can we find which interval contains that middle student?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_zsj1q57l"><p xml:id="auto_b6l4fl8p">What is cumulative frequency and how does it help us?</p></li>
            </ul>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

    <activity xml:id="auto_yjhrrpyj">
        <p xml:id="auto_adbn6itl">
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_tp8si4lj">
            Using the pocket money data provided below:
        </p>
        <table xml:id="auto_ofp571ac">
            <title>Pocket Money Distribution</title>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                    <cell>Pocket Money (Ksh)</cell>
                    <cell><m>100 - 199</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>200 - 299</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>300 - 399</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>400 - 499</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>500 - 599</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row halign="left" header="yes"> 
                    <cell>Frequency</cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>22</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p xml:id="auto_bzutrzcq">
            <ol>
                <li xml:id="auto_qxz4hs4o"><p xml:id="auto_yng7ud36">Construct a Cumulative Frequency column for this data.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_7lkr00ey"><p xml:id="auto_qev07dgw">Identify the class interval where the middle student lies.</p></li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Structured Instruction</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_1tyyre6y">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_9jpw9c2j">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_xwlyq1yk">10 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_r1gjf8e4">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_v8qiv0i2">To formalize the median formula for grouped data: Median = L + ((n/2 − CF) / F) × C, and the step-by-step process for identifying the median class and applying interpolation.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <insight xml:id="auto_s6k7rxyn">
        <p xml:id="auto_qpyartyw">
            <term>Calculating Median</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_hmh2ry03">
            For grouped frequency data, we use interpolation to estimate the median using the following formula:
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_j3f984xe">
            <md>
                <mrow> \text{Median} = \amp  L + \left(\frac{\frac{n}{2} - CF}{F}\right)\times C</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_fa2qga8e">
            Where:
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_enw1ebsu"><p xml:id="auto_nq3i3bq9"><m>L</m> = Lower boundary of the median class.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_mm7oorwz"><p xml:id="auto_cdlku2jf"><m>n</m> = Sum of all frequencies (<m>\sum f</m>).</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_jirkcy4f"><p xml:id="auto_v6hgn3ar"><m>CF</m> = Cumulative frequency <term>before</term> the median class.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_m8xthvoc"><p xml:id="auto_bs15rdfg"><m>F</m> = Frequency of the median class itself.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_j2xgm1u4"><p xml:id="auto_kfcvyr24"><m>C</m> = Class width.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </insight>


    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Practice and Application</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_wwglgk09">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_ds595nif">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_hwpie76s">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_6mqasryq">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_hbkqks70">To apply the grouped data median formula to estimate the median from frequency distribution tables.</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_6pe6ujp4">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_2owxcx3x">Work through examples with learners step by step. Circulate during independent practice and provide assistance where needed.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <example xml:id="auto_eyw7t9el">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_aw1l7j78">
                The data below represents the times (in seconds) recorded in the heats of a <m>100</m> m race. The data has been grouped into intervals of width 0.5 seconds.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_gfjcpv4f">
                Estimate the median time based on the frequency table below.
            </p>
            <table xml:id="auto_4qqab87i">
                <title>Race Times</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Class Interval</cell>
                        <cell>Frequency</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell><m>11.5 - 11.9</m></cell><cell><m>2</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>12.0 - 12.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>12.5 - 12.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>13.0 - 13.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>13.5 - 13.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>14.0 - 14.4</m></cell><cell><m>6</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>14.5 - 14.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>15.0 - 15.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>15.5 - 15.9</m></cell><cell><m>1</m></cell></row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_e8huvxpo">
                First, we add a Cumulative Frequency (CF) column to find the position of the median.
            </p>
            <table xml:id="auto_a60lao8i">
                <title>Cumulative Frequency Table</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Class Interval</cell>
                        <cell>Frequency (<m>f</m>)</cell>
                        <cell>Cumulative Frequency (<m>CF</m>)</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell><m>11.5 - 11.9</m></cell><cell><m>2</m></cell><cell><m>2</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>12.0 - 12.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell><cell><m>6</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>12.5 - 12.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell><cell><m>11</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>13.0 - 13.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell><cell><m>15</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>13.5 - 13.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell><cell><m>20</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>14.0 - 14.4</m></cell><cell><m>6</m></cell><cell><m>26</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>14.5 - 14.9</m></cell><cell><m>5</m></cell><cell><m>31</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>15.0 - 15.4</m></cell><cell><m>4</m></cell><cell><m>35</m></cell></row>
                    <row><cell><m>15.5 - 15.9</m></cell><cell><m>1</m></cell><cell><m>36</m></cell></row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
            <p xml:id="auto_eyhbnntg">
                Step 1: Locate the Median Class
                Total frequency <m>n = 36</m>. The median position is <m>\frac{36}{2} = 18</m>.
                Looking at the CF column, the value 18 falls within the interval where the cumulative frequency rises from 15 to 20. 
                Therefore, the <term>median class is 13.5 - 13.9</term>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_lbxhnjuw">
                Step 2: Apply the Formula
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_pqautnr5"><m>L = 13.5</m> (Lower boundary)</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_4i99y8om"><m>n = 36</m>, so <m>\frac{n}{2} = 18</m></li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_9xa0pw1v"><m>CF = 15</m> (Value before the median class)</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_lyb2b2bn"><m>F = 5</m> (Frequency of the median class)</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_zx92kqf6"><m>C = 0.5</m> (Class width)</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_n1sq6u7h">
                <md>
                    <mrow> \text{Median} = \amp  13.5 + \left(\frac{18 - 15}{5}\right)\times 0.5</mrow>
                    <mrow> =  \amp 13.5 + \left(\frac{3}{5}\times 0.5\right)</mrow>
                    <mrow> =  \amp 13.5 + 0.3</mrow>
                    <mrow> =  \amp 13.8</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_vid8kccs">
                Thus, the median time is <m>13.8</m> seconds.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

    <example xml:id="auto_e6oivujv">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_uuzphyrv">
                The marks obtained by 40 students in a mathematics test are:
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_6nbzsviw">
                <m>42, 55, 47, 61, 50, 38, 44, 49, 53, 60,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_yk6qm9v9">
                <m>41, 48, 52, 46, 57, 51, 39, 62, 45, 58,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_fhtcw7xb">
                <m>43, 56, 54, 59, 63, 40, 37, 64, 36, 65,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_h0yb01qj">
                <m>47, 49, 50, 52, 55, 51, 48, 53, 60, 62</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_ijfa123m">
                Using <m>6</m> class intervals, find the median mark.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_shqhzkwj">
                <ol marker="Step 1:">
                    <li xml:id="auto_dvttpkfg">
                        <p xml:id="auto_5wcvf7e4">
                            <term>Determine the range</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_hp7846zn">
                            Maximum value <m>= 65</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_d2l7x5r8">
                            Minimum value <m>= 36</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_xdpeb7mc">
                            Range <m>= 65 - 36 = 29</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_ljnzxcc5">
                        <p xml:id="auto_0wa7rumi">
                            <term>Decide class width</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_tc6ofkkr">
                            Number of classes <m>= 6</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_3uygziwa">
                            Class width <m>=</m> Range <m>\div</m> Number of classes <m>= 29 \div 6 \approx 4.83 </m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_ynmxavyu">
                            We can therefore use a class width of <m>5</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_o04yvc45">
                        <p xml:id="auto_s6axud9d">
                            <term>Complete the frequency table</term>
                        </p>
                        <tabular left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium" top="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Class Interval</cell>
                                <cell>Frequency (f)</cell>
                                <cell>Cumulative Frequency (CF)</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>36-40</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>14-45</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>46-50</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>19</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>51-55</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>28</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>56-60</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>34</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>61-65</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>40</m></cell>
                            </row>

                        </tabular>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_kl5yuf5s">
                        <p xml:id="auto_8bcgoyhz">
                            <term>Find the median Class</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_wdmyed4v">
                            Number of observations, <m>n = 40</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_c2m5bam6">
                            Median class <m>=</m> the class containing <m>\frac{n}{2} = 20^{th}</m> observation.
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_sfhchwv3">
                            From CF: <m>19^{th}</m> observation is in <m>46-50</m>, while <m>28^{th}</m> observation is in <m>51-55</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_qc5iyubf">
                            So the median class <m>= 51-55</m> since that is where the <m>20^{th}</m> observation fall.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_j8s10dww">
                        <p xml:id="auto_a3fpj9tu">
                            <term>Apply the median formula</term>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_xytjsqhu">
                            <md>
                                <mrow>\text{Median} = \amp L + \left(\frac{\frac{n}{2} - CF}{F}\right)\times h </mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 50.5 + \left(\frac{\frac{40}{2} - 19}{9}\right) \times 5</mrow>
                                <mrow> = \amp 50.0  + \frac{5}{9}</mrow>
                                <mrow> \text{Median} = \amp 51.05555</mrow>
                            </md>
                            
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_1zhsww4h">
                            Median mark<m> \approx 51.06</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

